Abdominal Pain Management
protocolId = 19
--------------------------------------------------

EMTA
<table><tr><td>1.<td>Perform general patient management.
<tr><td>2.<td>Assess mechanism of injury and / or nature of illness.
<tr><td>3.<td>Administer Oxygen to maintain <i><u>SPO</u></i><sub>2</sub> 94 - 99%
<tr><td>4.<td>Allow the patient to lie in a comfortable position.
<tr><td>5.<td>If shock is present, without pulsating masses, refer to <i><u>Shock protocol</u></i>.

EMTB
<table><tr><td>1.<td>Perform general patient management.
<tr><td>2.<td>Assess mechanism of injury and / or nature of illness.
<tr><td>3.<td>Administer Oxygen to maintain <i><u>SPO</u></i><sub>2</sub> 94 - 99%
<tr><td>4.<td>Allow the patient to lie in a comfortable position.
<tr><td>5.<td>If shock is present, without pulsating masses, refer to <i><u>Shock protocol</u></i>.
<tr><td>6.<td>Place patient on cardiac monitor and obtain a <i><u>12 lead ECG</u></i> if indicated.
<tr><td>7.<td>Transport and perform ongoing assessment as indicated.

EMTEN
<table><tr><td>1.<td>Perform general patient management.
<tr><td>2.<td>Assess mechanism of injury and / or nature of illness.
<tr><td>3.<td>Administer Oxygen to maintain <i><u>SPO</u></i><sub>2</sub> 94 - 99%
<tr><td>4.<td>Allow the patient to lie in a comfortable position.
<tr><td>5.<td>If shock is present, without pulsating masses, refer to <i><u>Shock protocol</u></i>.
<tr><td>6.<td>Place patient on cardiac monitor and obtain a <i><u>12 lead ECG</u></i> if indicated.
<tr><td>7.<td>Initiate IV of Normal Saline KVO.
<tr><td>8.<td>Transport and perform ongoing assessment as indicated.

EMTI/EMTP
<table><tr><td>1.<td>Perform general patient management.
<tr><td>2.<td>Assess mechanism of injury and / or nature of illness.
<tr><td>3.<td>Administer Oxygen to maintain <i><u>SPO</u></i><sub>2</sub> 94 - 99%
<tr><td>4.<td>Allow the patient to lie in a comfortable position.
<tr><td>5.<td>If shock is present, without pulsating masses, refer to <i><u>Shock protocol</u></i>.
<tr><td>6.<td>Place patient on cardiac monitor and obtain a <i><u>12 lead ECG</u></i> if indicated.
<tr><td>7.<td>Initiate IV of Normal Saline KVO.
<tr><td>8.<td>Administer <i><u>ONDANSETRON</u></i> 0.1 mg / kg slow IVP over 2 - 5 minutes, max 4.0 mg per dose, as needed, per <i><u>Nausea and Vomiting Patient Care Protocol</u></i>.
<tr><td>9.<td>Treat pain if indicated. Refer to <i><u>pain management</u></i> guideline.
<tr><td>10.<td>Transport and perform ongoing assessment as indicated.
